Oh, yeah, I've heard of that.

256
00:17:16,326 --> 00:17:17,327
Huh.

257
00:17:33,969 --> 00:17:35,971
[water dripping]

258
00:17:45,773 --> 00:17:47,775
[metal squeaking]

259
00:17:50,360 --> 00:17:51,671
It works?

260
00:17:51,695 --> 00:17:53,530
Somebody must have greased it.

261
00:18:02,164 --> 00:18:04,208
[Ellie] Can you imagine
being up there?

262
00:18:06,835 --> 00:18:08,962
- Would you like to?
- Like to what?

263
00:18:09,963 --> 00:18:11,006
Go to space?

264
00:18:25,187 --> 00:18:26,164
[softly gasps]

265
00:18:26,188 --> 00:18:28,416
[birdsong]

266
00:18:28,440 --> 00:18:30,543
[Ellie] [whispering]
Is it real?

267
00:18:30,567 --> 00:18:33,278
It's real.
That one went up and back.

268
00:18:34,113 --> 00:18:36,281
Apollo 15, 1971.

269
00:18:39,076 --> 00:18:42,538
[♪ gentle music playing]

270
00:18:53,423 --> 00:18:54,675
Well, open it.

271
00:18:56,426 --> 00:18:58,428
[Joel chuckles]

272
00:19:01,932 --> 00:19:04,452
[metal door creaking]

273
00:19:04,476 --> 00:19:06,353
- [whispering] You got it.
- [Ellie sighs]

274
00:19:08,772 --> 00:19:10,041
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

275
00:19:10,065 --> 00:19:12,043
You're going up to space.

276
00:19:12,067 --> 00:19:13,402
You need a helmet.

277
00:19:16,738 --> 00:19:18,157
[grunting]

278
00:19:21,410 --> 00:19:22,578
Pick one.

279
00:19:41,513 --> 00:19:43,515
[glass shattering]

280
00:19:56,737 --> 00:19:59,740
[♪ gentle music playing]

281
00:20:04,203 --> 00:20:06,139
How's it smell in there?

282
00:20:06,163 --> 00:20:09,017
Like space, and dust.

283
00:20:09,041 --> 00:20:11,293
Well, good.
Then, you're ready.

284
00:20:25,724 --> 00:20:27,559
[grunting]

285
00:20:32,189 --> 00:20:33,273
[hatch door thuds]

286
00:20:34,483 --> 00:20:36,711
[Ellie imitating lasers firing]

287
00:20:36,735 --> 00:20:38,654
[imitating static]

288
00:20:39,363 --> 00:20:42,467
People of Discovery, set!
Abort!

289
00:20:42,491 --> 00:20:44,534
[switches clicking]

290
00:20:47,788 --> 00:20:49,623
They sat right here.

291
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:53,210
[Ellie chuckles]

292
00:20:54,336 --> 00:20:57,357
- Happy birthday, kiddo.
- What's this?

293
00:20:57,381 --> 00:21:01,986
This is something that took
a mighty effort to find.

294
00:21:02,010 --> 00:21:03,178
Play it.

295
00:21:13,397 --> 00:21:14,523
[seat creaking]

296
00:21:19,987 --> 00:21:21,839
Close your eyes.

297
00:21:21,863 --> 00:21:23,490
It'll be worth it.

298
00:21:25,993 --> 00:21:27,160
[Walkman clicking]

299
00:21:28,787 --> 00:21:31,599
[NASA Public Affairs Officer]
<i>Thirty seconds and counting.</i>

300
00:21:31,623 --> 00:21:33,518
<i>Astronauts report it feels good.</i>

301
00:21:33,542 --> 00:21:35,335
<i>T-minus 25 seconds.</i>

302
00:21:38,547 --> 00:21:40,173
<i>Twenty seconds and counting.</i>

303
00:21:42,342 --> 00:21:45,780
<i>T-minus 15 seconds.
Guidance is internal.</i>

304
00:21:45,804 --> 00:21:49,701
<i>Twelve, eleven, ten, nine.</i>

305
00:21:49,725 --> 00:21:51,536
<i>Ignition sequence starts.</i>

306
00:21:51,560 --> 00:21:52,787
[spacecraft whooshing, rattling]

307
00:21:52,811 --> 00:21:56,207
<i>Six, five, four, three,</i>

308
00:21:56,231 --> 00:21:58,876
<i>two, one, zero.</i>

309
00:21:58,900 --> 00:22:01,546
- [rockets booming]
<i>- All engines running.</i>

310
00:22:01,570 --> 00:22:03,715
<i>Liftoff!
We have a liftoff,</i>

311
00:22:03,739 --> 00:22:07,492
<i>32 minutes past the hour,
liftoff on Apollo 11.</i>

312
00:22:13,040 --> 00:22:15,042
[rattling and booming
decreasing]

313
00:22:16,626 --> 00:22:19,629
[♪ gentle music playing]

314
00:22:46,114 --> 00:22:48,116
[birdsong]

315
00:22:50,160 --> 00:22:52,096
I do okay?

316
00:22:52,120 --> 00:22:53,622
Are you kidding me?

317
00:22:56,416 --> 00:22:58,418
[both laughing]

318
00:23:01,213 --> 00:23:02,506
[Ellie sighs]

319
00:23:16,853 --> 00:23:18,146
This is nice.

320
00:23:19,773 --> 00:23:22,609
- We should do this more.
- Yeah. In.

321
00:23:33,620 --> 00:23:34,996
You okay?

322
00:23:36,540 --> 00:23:37,624
Yeah.

323
00:23:56,601 --> 00:23:58,603
[rain pattering]

324
00:24:13,660 --> 00:24:15,662
[rain continues]

325
00:24:23,753 --> 00:24:26,899
[Ellie] [giggling, muffled]
Stop.

326
00:24:26,923 --> 00:24:28,967
[people laughing]

327
00:24:31,511 --> 00:24:33,698
[laughter continues]

328
00:24:33,722 --> 00:24:35,182
- [banging]
- [Ellie] Fuck.

329
00:24:37,058 --> 00:24:38,560
Joel, what the fuck?

330
00:24:39,436 --> 00:24:41,205
Exactly.
What the fuck?

331
00:24:41,229 --> 00:24:43,124
- Get outta here.
- No, wait.

332
00:24:43,148 --> 00:24:44,709
What-- what are you
even doing here?

333
00:24:44,733 --> 00:24:46,127
You're supposed to be on patrol.

334
00:24:46,151 --> 00:24:49,213
I came home early to...
surprise you for your birthday.

335
00:24:49,237 --> 00:24:51,948
- [Ellie] [whispering] Oh, yeah.
- Seventeen, by the way.

336
00:24:52,532 --> 00:24:54,409
Well, I'm 19, so...

337
00:24:55,785 --> 00:24:57,454
I'm gonna go.

338
00:24:59,998 --> 00:25:02,375
- Fuck is that?
- Fuck.

339
00:25:05,337 --> 00:25:07,398
It's not done yet,
it's gonna look better when I fill in--

340
00:25:07,422 --> 00:25:08,715
- [Joel] Leave.
- Right.

341
00:25:12,093 --> 00:25:13,136
[Ellie sighing]

342
00:25:19,309 --> 00:25:21,520
So, all the teenage shit
all at once, huh?

343
00:25:22,854 --> 00:25:26,066
Drugs, and tattoos, and sex.

344
00:25:26,608 --> 00:25:29,319
Experimenting with, uh, with--
[stammering] with girls?

345
00:25:30,529 --> 00:25:33,740
It wasn't sex, and it
wasn't a fucking experiment.

346
00:25:36,743 --> 00:25:38,203
You don't know
what you're sayin'.

347
00:25:39,955 --> 00:25:41,915
We'll discuss this later,
when you're yourself.

348
00:25:44,084 --> 00:25:45,544
- [door slamming]
- [sighs]

349
00:25:46,795 --> 00:25:48,797
[thunder rumbling]

350
00:25:55,637 --> 00:25:57,639
[rain falling]

351
00:26:01,059 --> 00:26:03,061
[thunder continues rumbling]

352
00:26:09,025 --> 00:26:11,027
[rain pattering]

353
00:26:17,534 --> 00:26:19,536
[heavy thudding]

354
00:26:27,377 --> 00:26:29,379
[Ellie grunting]

355
00:26:33,008 --> 00:26:35,403
- The hell are you doing?
- Moving into the garage.

356
00:26:35,427 --> 00:26:37,596
The hell you are.
Ellie, let go.

357
00:26:38,305 --> 00:26:40,157
It's the middle of the night.
It's pissin' rain out there.

358
00:26:40,181 --> 00:26:41,867
Now, get this back on the bed.

359
00:26:41,891 --> 00:26:43,744
There's no heat
or running water in the garage.

360
00:26:43,768 --> 00:26:45,979
- You can't stay there.
- Okay, fine.

361
00:26:47,439 --> 00:26:49,566
Okay, you want to have
this conversation? Fine.

362
00:26:50,692 --> 00:26:52,587
You may not like the rules,
but this is my house.

363
00:26:52,611 --> 00:26:55,047
No, it isn't.
You don't own it.

364
00:26:55,071 --> 00:26:58,217
They gave it to you.
Sorry, to us.

365
00:26:58,241 --> 00:26:59,993
You don't own anything.

366
00:27:01,077 --> 00:27:03,079
[rain continues pattering]

367
00:27:11,171 --> 00:27:13,274
Look, I'm s-sorry
that I got a tattoo,

368
00:27:13,298 --> 00:27:16,259
and smoked weed,
and fooled around with a girl.

369
00:27:18,345 --> 00:27:19,679
Except, I'm not.

370
00:27:22,724 --> 00:27:23,850
Maybe, um...

371
00:27:28,271 --> 00:27:30,440
Maybe it's a good thing
for you to have your own space.

372
00:27:32,984 --> 00:27:34,462
Just give me a few days

373
00:27:34,486 --> 00:27:36,363
and let me fix things up
a little out there.

374
00:27:38,573 --> 00:27:39,574
Okay.

375
00:27:43,453 --> 00:27:44,454
Come on.

376
00:28:00,970 --> 00:28:02,490
[sighs] Thanks.

377
00:28:02,514 --> 00:28:03,556
Sure.

378
00:28:06,976 --> 00:28:08,144
Can I see?

379
00:28:14,526 --> 00:28:16,528
- Did it hurt?
- Yeah.

380
00:28:19,072 --> 00:28:20,490
But kinda good.

381
00:28:24,202 --> 00:28:25,704
It's actually not bad.

382
00:28:27,038 --> 00:28:31,334
Better than the, uh,
one I made on your guitar anyway.

383
00:28:37,465 --> 00:28:39,300
I never did ask.
What is it with the moths?

384
00:28:41,511 --> 00:28:43,656
Um, nothing. Just--

385
00:28:43,680 --> 00:28:47,201
I just read about them
in a book on dreams and stuff.

386
00:28:47,225 --> 00:28:48,953
It's kind of symbolic.

387
00:28:48,977 --> 00:28:50,395
Oh, right.

388
00:28:52,439 --> 00:28:57,360
Yeah, like change and--
and growin' and such.

389
00:29:01,322 --> 00:29:02,490
It's late.

390
00:29:03,283 --> 00:29:04,284
Yeah.

391
00:29:05,994 --> 00:29:07,078
Well, good night.

392
00:29:08,329 --> 00:29:09,330
Night.

393
00:29:12,083 --> 00:29:13,960
[door creaking]

394
00:29:18,923 --> 00:29:20,925
- [door opens]
- [people chattering]

395
00:29:24,596 --> 00:29:26,598
[door closes]

396
00:29:28,475 --> 00:29:29,517
[Joel] Hey.

397
00:29:32,270 --> 00:29:35,940
You guys study, uh,
dreams and stuff, right?

398
00:29:37,317 --> 00:29:39,503
Is there a "Doctor Is In" sign
on me like Lucy

399
00:29:39,527 --> 00:29:41,446
from fuckin' <i>Peanuts?</i>

400
00:29:44,407 --> 00:29:47,845
Yes, some doctors
studied dreams.

401
00:29:47,869 --> 00:29:49,889
The dumb ones, mostly.

402
00:29:49,913 --> 00:29:51,122
So, a moth.

403
00:29:52,207 --> 00:29:55,895
That probably means
change and-- and growth?

404
00:29:55,919 --> 00:29:57,629
No, that would be a butterfly.

405
00:29:58,671 --> 00:30:00,858
Oh.
So, what's a moth?

406
00:30:00,882 --> 00:30:02,050
Death.

407
00:30:03,384 --> 00:30:04,928
If you believe in that shit.

408
00:30:14,813 --> 00:30:15,814
Why?

409
00:30:23,029 --> 00:30:25,031
[footsteps receding]

410
00:30:27,158 --> 00:30:28,701
[door opens]

411
00:30:30,036 --> 00:30:31,639
[door closes]

412
00:30:31,663 --> 00:30:34,707
[♪ soft music playing]

413
00:30:45,552 --> 00:30:47,554
[poster rustling]

414
00:31:19,085 --> 00:31:21,462
Okay, so I've been thinking...

415
00:31:22,589 --> 00:31:25,109
or wondering--
no, thinking,

416
00:31:25,133 --> 00:31:27,093
uh, for a while now...

417
00:31:28,094 --> 00:31:30,263
about Salt Lake City.

418
00:31:32,015 --> 00:31:33,808
I just want to understand it.

419
00:31:35,810 --> 00:31:38,563
So, I wrote down some questions.

420
00:31:39,856 --> 00:31:40,857
Okay?

421
00:31:43,276 --> 00:31:44,277
Okay.

422
00:31:53,202 --> 00:31:55,848
One, if the Fireflies

423
00:31:55,872 --> 00:31:58,392
spotted us a mile
from the hospital,

424
00:31:58,416 --> 00:32:01,502
how did they get surprised
by an entire group of Raiders?

425
00:32:05,423 --> 00:32:07,026
Two.

426
00:32:07,050 --> 00:32:10,321
If the Raiders could
kill all those soldiers,

427
00:32:10,345 --> 00:32:14,199
and Marlene, and you had
to carry me the whole time,

428
00:32:14,223 --> 00:32:15,683
how did we get away?

429
00:32:17,268 --> 00:32:19,663
Three, if there are dozens
of immune people,

430
00:32:19,687 --> 00:32:21,648
- why hasn't anyone heard--
- [knocking]

431
00:32:22,690 --> 00:32:23,918
[knocking]

432
00:32:23,942 --> 00:32:24,984
[Joel] Ellie?

433
00:32:26,611 --> 00:32:27,862
Uh, coming.

434
00:32:32,408 --> 00:32:34,494
- [clearing throat]
- Whoa.

435
00:32:35,328 --> 00:32:37,181
Already dressed.

436
00:32:37,205 --> 00:32:39,016
I figured I'd be waking you up.

437
00:32:39,040 --> 00:32:41,518
Uh, nope.
I had trouble sleeping.

438
00:32:41,542 --> 00:32:42,686
Huh.

439
00:32:42,710 --> 00:32:44,188
Well, guess what?
That works out great

440
00:32:44,212 --> 00:32:45,856
for your birthday present.

441
00:32:45,880 --> 00:32:48,299
You're 19
and you've been patient.

442
00:32:49,467 --> 00:32:51,362
So, I told 'em
I was okay with it.

443
00:32:51,386 --> 00:32:54,389
- With what?
- Your first patrol.

444
00:32:56,766 --> 00:32:58,559
- I'll grab my coat.
- And a gun.

445
00:33:04,941 --> 00:33:07,461
[crow cawing]

446
00:33:07,485 --> 00:33:09,529
[horse chortling]

447
00:33:11,030 --> 00:33:12,883
[Ellie] So, what's the record
for number of kills

448
00:33:12,907 --> 00:33:14,593
on a training run?

449
00:33:14,617 --> 00:33:17,638
Zero. This is
the safest trail we got.

450
00:33:17,662 --> 00:33:18,889
Gotta start easy.

451
00:33:18,913 --> 00:33:20,873
Ah, great.
Happy birthday to me.

452
00:33:22,083 --> 00:33:24,937
- Come on, binoculars.
- Why? There's nothing out here.

453
00:33:24,961 --> 00:33:27,338
I know, but this is about
learnin' the ropes.

454
00:33:28,256 --> 00:33:30,049
So, pretend, okay?

455
00:33:32,343 --> 00:33:34,905
It's part of the rules.
You stick with your partner,

456
00:33:34,929 --> 00:33:37,557
scan the countryside,
be ready for anything.

457
00:33:38,099 --> 00:33:39,475
- Oh, shit.
- What?

458
00:33:41,227 --> 00:33:43,938
There's a little squirrel
fucking a big squirrel!

459
00:33:44,856 --> 00:33:46,149
We should probably report that.

460
00:33:48,609 --> 00:33:50,278
Fine, we'll skip
the scannin' for now.

461
00:33:54,949 --> 00:33:56,927
But this is nice, right?

462
00:33:56,951 --> 00:33:59,912
Reminds me of the old days,
just you and me on the trail.

463
00:34:00,997 --> 00:34:02,933
I know you got stuff going on,
but it'd be nice

464
00:34:02,957 --> 00:34:05,519
if we could do
this kind of thing more often.

465
00:34:05,543 --> 00:34:06,794
Spend time together.

466
00:34:10,089 --> 00:34:11,090
Yeah.

467
00:34:15,803 --> 00:34:17,781
- You okay?
- Yeah.

468
00:34:17,805 --> 00:34:19,450
- It's just, you look...
- No, I--

469
00:34:19,474 --> 00:34:21,326
- There's nothin' on your mind?
- No, nothing.

470
00:34:21,350 --> 00:34:23,870
[dispatcher] [over radio]
<i>Cache Creek, this is Jackson. Come in.</i>

471
00:34:26,898 --> 00:34:29,710
- Go for Cache Creek.
<i>- Infected north of Pinnacle.</i>

472
00:34:29,734 --> 00:34:32,629
<i>Eugene and Adam need backup.
You're the closest we've got.</i>

473
00:34:32,653 --> 00:34:34,673
- [horse chortling]
- I'll be there in ten.

474
00:34:34,697 --> 00:34:36,300
Tell them to dig in.

475
00:34:36,324 --> 00:34:37,676
- Go back to Jackson.
- No.

476
00:34:37,700 --> 00:34:39,511
Ellie, it's not safe.
Go back.

477
00:34:39,535 --> 00:34:41,138
I'm not your fucking kid, Joel.

478
00:34:41,162 --> 00:34:43,289
I'm your partner.
We stick together.

479
00:34:46,876 --> 00:34:48,812
[horse neighing]

480
00:34:48,836 --> 00:34:50,296
[Joel clicking tongue]

481
00:34:53,424 --> 00:34:56,427
[♪ ominous music playing]

482
00:35:16,364 --> 00:35:19,158
We'll hike down from here.
Faster than the switchback.

483
00:35:34,257 --> 00:35:37,260
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

484
00:35:51,482 --> 00:35:53,943
- [distant screeching]
- [distant gunshot]

485
00:35:56,487 --> 00:35:58,215
You remember what I taught you?

486
00:35:58,239 --> 00:35:59,782
I'm your back.
You're mine.

487
00:36:07,915 --> 00:36:09,917
[♪ suspenseful music continues]

488
00:36:23,472 --> 00:36:24,682
[mysterious noise approaching]

489
00:36:28,686 --> 00:36:30,688
[horse whinnying]

490
00:36:35,735 --> 00:36:36,861
Come on.

491
00:36:40,865 --> 00:36:42,867
[leaves crunching]

492
00:36:45,828 --> 00:36:48,331
♪

493
00:37:05,139 --> 00:37:06,557
Oh, shit.
Eugene.

494
00:37:07,308 --> 00:37:08,309
[Joel] Ellie.

495
00:37:13,397 --> 00:37:14,625
You clean?

496
00:37:14,649 --> 00:37:15,650
Uh...

497
00:37:17,318 --> 00:37:18,402
Uh...

498
00:37:19,487 --> 00:37:20,488
No.

499
00:37:25,117 --> 00:37:26,720
- Are there any more?
- Joel.

500
00:37:26,744 --> 00:37:28,663
Are there any more?

501
00:37:29,413 --> 00:37:30,873
Other than me?

502
00:37:34,377 --> 00:37:35,378
No.

503
00:37:37,546 --> 00:37:40,317
- Whoa.
- Okay, okay. Look.

504
00:37:40,341 --> 00:37:43,320
Please, I-- I-- I figure
I got about an hour.

505
00:37:43,344 --> 00:37:45,989
So, this is what we do.
We go back to the gate.

506
00:37:46,013 --> 00:37:48,325
They let Gail out,

507
00:37:48,349 --> 00:37:50,494
keeping her at a safe distance,
of course.

508
00:37:50,518 --> 00:37:52,728
And I-- I say...

509
00:37:53,854 --> 00:37:55,064
goodbye.

510
00:37:56,691 --> 00:37:57,858
We can't do that.

511
00:37:58,859 --> 00:38:00,486
Yes-- yes, we can.

512
00:38:05,116 --> 00:38:08,077
- Yes, we can.
- You're empty.

513
00:38:10,246 --> 00:38:11,247
[groaning]

514
00:38:12,456 --> 00:38:13,809
No. [stammering]

515
00:38:13,833 --> 00:38:16,520
Joel, I gotta go back.
I gotta see her.

516
00:38:16,544 --> 00:38:20,089
I got things I gotta tell her.

517
00:38:22,842 --> 00:38:24,403
Things.

518
00:38:24,427 --> 00:38:26,512
- You don't understand.
- I do.

519
00:38:27,513 --> 00:38:29,574
