clearly, from one to ten.

525
00:38:51,662 --> 00:38:54,891
One, two, three,

526
00:38:54,915 --> 00:38:56,893
four, five,

527
00:38:56,917 --> 00:39:00,230
six, seven, eight,

528
00:39:00,254 --> 00:39:02,840
nine, ten.

529
00:39:03,841 --> 00:39:05,277
He has time.

530
00:39:05,301 --> 00:39:07,178
We tie him up
and we bring him back.

531
00:39:09,638 --> 00:39:11,640
Joel, let him see
his fucking wife.

532
00:39:12,933 --> 00:39:14,268
Please.

533
00:39:15,811 --> 00:39:17,080
[sighs]

534
00:39:17,104 --> 00:39:19,315
[breathing heavily]

535
00:39:22,109 --> 00:39:24,129
Get the horses,
bring them down the trail.

536
00:39:24,153 --> 00:39:26,193
I'll start walkin' with him,
we'll meet up with you.

537
00:39:39,585 --> 00:39:40,669
I promise.

538
00:39:50,763 --> 00:39:52,181
Go ahead, ten feet.

539
00:39:53,265 --> 00:39:54,266
Thank you.

540
00:40:06,195 --> 00:40:08,197
[foliage rustling]

541
00:40:18,749 --> 00:40:20,751
[Eugene panting]

542
00:40:21,752 --> 00:40:24,922
It makes you cold.
The Cordyceps.

543
00:40:26,507 --> 00:40:28,342
I didn't expect that.

544
00:40:32,263 --> 00:40:35,683
[sighs]
Which, uh, way?

545
00:40:39,186 --> 00:40:40,271
Head right.

546
00:40:44,275 --> 00:40:46,277
[Eugene shivering]

547
00:40:59,957 --> 00:41:01,876
It's beautiful.

548
00:41:04,336 --> 00:41:06,839
[♪ ominous music playing]

549
00:41:08,632 --> 00:41:09,633
Oh.

550
00:41:11,927 --> 00:41:14,138
I need you to not turn around.

551
00:41:15,306 --> 00:41:16,908
No.

552
00:41:16,932 --> 00:41:18,410
Uh, you can't--

553
00:41:18,434 --> 00:41:20,370
you can't do this to me.

554
00:41:20,394 --> 00:41:22,622
Joel.

555
00:41:22,646 --> 00:41:25,375
If you have last words for her,
I'll pass them along.

556
00:41:25,399 --> 00:41:27,067
[Eugene]
Last words for her?

557
00:41:28,027 --> 00:41:31,572
No, no, I need--
I need her last words!

558
00:41:32,698 --> 00:41:34,116
For me!

559
00:41:36,619 --> 00:41:37,912
I'm dying.

560
00:41:39,038 --> 00:41:40,998
I'm terrified.
I, uh...

561
00:41:46,587 --> 00:41:47,880
I don't need a view.

562
00:41:51,300 --> 00:41:52,676
I need Gail.

563
00:41:55,304 --> 00:41:57,348
To see her face.
Please.

564
00:41:58,516 --> 00:42:00,851
Please let that be
the last thing I see.

565
00:42:06,524 --> 00:42:07,983
If you love someone...

566
00:42:10,986 --> 00:42:12,571
you can always see their face.

567
00:42:15,157 --> 00:42:18,369
[♪ somber music playing]

568
00:42:20,538 --> 00:42:22,039
[sighs]

569
00:42:30,881 --> 00:42:33,884
♪

570
00:42:49,900 --> 00:42:51,193
I see her.

571
00:42:53,571 --> 00:42:56,574
[♪ somber music
continues playing]

572
00:43:14,967 --> 00:43:16,969
[foliage rustling]

573
00:43:18,012 --> 00:43:20,014
[hoofbeats]

574
00:43:45,247 --> 00:43:46,415
I'm sorry.

575
00:44:08,604 --> 00:44:10,814
I'm gonna radio ahead
and let them know.

576
00:44:12,941 --> 00:44:17,464
When we get there,
I'll-- I'll tell Gail

577
00:44:17,488 --> 00:44:19,907
what she needs to know,
and nothin' more.

578
00:44:21,450 --> 00:44:22,868
It's the right thing to do.

579
00:44:26,580 --> 00:44:27,581
Ellie.

580
00:44:32,127 --> 00:44:33,545
I had no choice.

581
00:44:53,273 --> 00:44:55,275
[crow cawing]

582
00:45:14,962 --> 00:45:18,090
Uh, he was bit
when we found him.

583
00:45:19,800 --> 00:45:20,926
And, uh...

584
00:45:22,761 --> 00:45:24,847
Well, he wanted to tell you
that he loved you.

585
00:45:28,600 --> 00:45:32,038
And, uh, he wished he could say goodbye
to you in person

586
00:45:32,062 --> 00:45:34,040
but he didn't wanna
put you in danger.

587
00:45:34,064 --> 00:45:35,566
[crying] No, no.

588
00:45:36,191 --> 00:45:38,694
[Joel]
And he wasn't scared. He...

589
00:45:39,737 --> 00:45:41,155
He was brave.

590
00:45:44,366 --> 00:45:45,969
And he ended it himself.

591
00:45:45,993 --> 00:45:47,536
[sighs]

592
00:45:50,873 --> 00:45:52,875
[sobbing]

593
00:45:59,381 --> 00:46:00,799
[Ellie]
That's not what happened.

594
00:46:06,764 --> 00:46:09,558
He begged to see you.
He had time.

595
00:46:10,267 --> 00:46:12,704
Joel promised
to take him to you.

596
00:46:12,728 --> 00:46:14,271
He promised us both.

597
00:46:17,232 --> 00:46:20,068
[softly] And then,
Joel shot him in the head.

598
00:46:24,448 --> 00:46:26,450
[breathing heavily]

599
00:46:30,788 --> 00:46:31,955
That's...

600
00:46:35,334 --> 00:46:37,604
Get away. Please.

601
00:46:37,628 --> 00:46:39,671
Get away from me, please.

602
00:46:46,094 --> 00:46:47,429
You swore.

603
00:46:49,932 --> 00:46:51,767
[Gail sobbing]

604
00:46:55,395 --> 00:46:57,356
[Gail] [sobbing] No.

605
00:47:12,830 --> 00:47:15,833
[♪ "Little Sadie"
by Crooked Still playing]

606
00:47:17,334 --> 00:47:19,395
<i>♪ Standing on the corner
reading a bill ♪</i>

607
00:47:19,419 --> 00:47:21,231
<i>♪ And up stepped
the sheriff from Thomasville ♪</i>

608
00:47:21,255 --> 00:47:23,483
<i>♪ He said,
"Miss, is your name Brown? ♪</i>

609
00:47:23,507 --> 00:47:27,094
<i>♪ Remember the night
you shot Sadie down?" ♪</i>

610
00:47:28,262 --> 00:47:31,616
<i>♪ I said, oh yes, sir,
but my name is Lee ♪</i>

611
00:47:31,640 --> 00:47:33,660
<i>♪ And I murdered Little Sadie
in the first degree ♪</i>

612
00:47:33,684 --> 00:47:35,787
<i>♪ First degree
and second degree ♪</i>

613
00:47:35,811 --> 00:47:40,107
<i>♪ Got any papers,
will you read 'em to me? ♪</i>

614
00:47:46,905 --> 00:47:48,466
- [♪ song ends]
- [Dina laughing]

615
00:47:48,490 --> 00:47:49,926
That was good, yeah?

616
00:47:49,950 --> 00:47:51,285
[people cheering]

617
00:47:51,660 --> 00:47:53,096
Oh, okay.

618
00:47:53,120 --> 00:47:55,515
Yeah, he's fallin' apart.
I'm gonna get him to bed.

619
00:47:55,539 --> 00:47:58,142
- You're gonna miss the countdown.
- I'll come back after.

620
00:47:58,166 --> 00:48:00,103
[singer] Okay. The next one
is a little slower.

621
00:48:00,127 --> 00:48:01,813
Save me some of that.

622
00:48:01,837 --> 00:48:03,106
Say goodnight to Uncle Grumpy.

623
00:48:03,130 --> 00:48:05,817
- Goodnight, Uncle Grumpy.
- [Tommy chuckles]

624
00:48:05,841 --> 00:48:08,444
- Night, kiddo.
- See you next year.

625
00:48:08,468 --> 00:48:10,613
See you next year.

626
00:48:10,637 --> 00:48:13,640
[♪ "Ecstasy"
by Crooked Still playing]

627
00:48:20,814 --> 00:48:22,649
- [Maria] You okay?
- Hm?

628
00:48:24,151 --> 00:48:25,319
Yeah, I'm fine.

629
00:48:27,237 --> 00:48:29,966
What I said today
about you being a refugee

630
00:48:29,990 --> 00:48:31,968
probably came off as ungrateful.

631
00:48:31,992 --> 00:48:34,995
- No, it's okay.
- Well, I am grateful.

632
00:48:35,913 --> 00:48:38,182
You mean a lot to us.
To all of us.

633
00:48:38,206 --> 00:48:40,351
But especially to me and Tommy.

634
00:48:40,375 --> 00:48:44,171
What I'm trying to say is,
Uncle Grumpy is family.

635
00:48:45,255 --> 00:48:47,859
And family helps each other out,

636
00:48:47,883 --> 00:48:49,319
if you need it.

637
00:48:49,343 --> 00:48:52,322
<i>♪ Oh, when shall I see
Jesus and reign... ♪</i>

638
00:48:52,346 --> 00:48:54,556
Hey, it's a family event.

639
00:48:55,849 --> 00:48:56,850
Sorry.

640
00:48:59,019 --> 00:49:00,705
Sorry.

641
00:49:00,729 --> 00:49:03,082
In a church.
Dykes.

642
00:49:03,106 --> 00:49:04,709
- [Ellie] Fuck did you just say?
- [Dina] Ellie, no.

643
00:49:04,733 --> 00:49:05,859
Ellie, hey. No.

644
00:49:06,693 --> 00:49:07,879
[crowd gasping]

645
00:49:07,903 --> 00:49:09,488
You get the hell out of here.

646
00:49:10,197 --> 00:49:11,841
[Maria]
Seth. Let's...

647
00:49:11,865 --> 00:49:14,928
- [Seth grunting]
- Let's take a walk.

648
00:49:14,952 --> 00:49:16,703
Come on.
Let's go.

649
00:49:19,039 --> 00:49:20,082
Are you okay?

650
00:49:21,416 --> 00:49:22,876
What is wrong with you?

651
00:49:26,755 --> 00:49:29,424
I don't need your fucking help.

652
00:49:37,975 --> 00:49:38,976
Right.

653
00:49:43,397 --> 00:49:46,400
[♪ gentle, somber music playing]

654
00:50:07,337 --> 00:50:09,339
[♪ strums guitar]

655
00:50:10,799 --> 00:50:12,801
♪

656
00:50:23,979 --> 00:50:25,981
[♪ guitar continues
playing faintly]

657
00:50:30,694 --> 00:50:31,820
[♪ stops playing]

658
00:51:44,559 --> 00:51:45,811
What are you drinking?

659
00:51:47,771 --> 00:51:48,772
Coffee.

660
00:51:49,773 --> 00:51:51,900
- Where'd you get it?
- Um...

661
00:51:53,151 --> 00:51:55,379
[smacks lips] The people that
came through last week.

662
00:51:55,403 --> 00:51:57,924
- Mm.
- I'm a little embarrassed

663
00:51:57,948 --> 00:52:00,075
for what I traded
to get it, but...

664
00:52:01,326 --> 00:52:02,786
it's not bad.

665
00:52:13,213 --> 00:52:14,840
I had Seth under control.

666
00:52:17,551 --> 00:52:19,695
Yeah, I know.

667
00:52:19,719 --> 00:52:22,597
And I don't wanna ever hear
about you taking me off patrol again.

668
00:52:25,267 --> 00:52:26,268
Okay.

669
00:52:34,025 --> 00:52:35,402
So, Dina.

670
00:52:38,029 --> 00:52:40,299
Is she your girlfriend now?

671
00:52:40,323 --> 00:52:42,659
No. No, she...

672
00:52:44,828 --> 00:52:47,747
It was just one kiss.
Didn't mean anything.

673
00:52:50,167 --> 00:52:51,668
I don't know why she did that.

674
00:52:54,212 --> 00:52:55,213
But...

675
00:52:57,090 --> 00:52:58,216
you do like her?

676
00:53:02,262 --> 00:53:04,723
[sighs]
I'm so stupid.

677
00:53:08,393 --> 00:53:11,354
Look, I don't know what
Dina's intentions are, but...

678
00:53:15,275 --> 00:53:16,902
well, she'd be lucky
to have you.

679
00:53:20,572 --> 00:53:22,199
You're such an asshole.

680
00:53:27,704 --> 00:53:28,997
You lied to me.

681
00:53:30,790 --> 00:53:33,352
You looked me in the eyes
and you lied,

682
00:53:33,376 --> 00:53:35,170
and it was the same face.

683
00:53:36,421 --> 00:53:38,548
Same fucking look.

684
00:53:43,178 --> 00:53:44,804
But I think I knew already.

685
00:53:47,515 --> 00:53:49,226
I knew this whole time.

686
00:53:55,732 --> 00:53:57,651
So, I'm gonna give you
one last chance.

687
00:54:00,028 --> 00:54:02,030
Tell me what happened
with the Fireflies.

688
00:54:03,615 --> 00:54:06,493
If you lie to me again,
we're done.

689
00:54:16,586 --> 00:54:18,088
Were there other immune people?

690
00:54:33,937 --> 00:54:35,522
Were there Raiders?

691
00:54:45,031 --> 00:54:46,616
Could they have made a cure?

692
00:55:03,466 --> 00:55:04,467
[sniffling]

693
00:55:08,305 --> 00:55:09,597
Did you--

694
00:55:16,187 --> 00:55:17,647
And Marlene?

695
00:55:24,738 --> 00:55:26,031
[sighs]

696
00:55:27,198 --> 00:55:28,450
Making a cure...

697
00:55:31,369 --> 00:55:32,620
would've killed you.

698
00:55:34,331 --> 00:55:36,225
Then, I was supposed to die.

699
00:55:36,249 --> 00:55:37,560
[sniffling]
That was my purpose.

700
00:55:37,584 --> 00:55:39,145
My life would have
fucking mattered!

701
00:55:39,169 --> 00:55:40,837
But you took that from me!

702
00:55:41,838 --> 00:55:43,548
You took it from everyone.

703
00:55:45,675 --> 00:55:46,676
Yes.

704
00:55:47,510 --> 00:55:48,511
[sighs]

705
00:55:49,971 --> 00:55:51,431
And I'll pay the price...

706
00:55:53,016 --> 00:55:55,143
because you're gonna
turn away from me.

707
00:55:56,227 --> 00:55:58,438
[breathing heavily]

708
00:56:00,148 --> 00:56:03,026
But if somehow I had
a second chance at that moment...

709
00:56:06,988 --> 00:56:08,448
I would do it all over again.

710
00:56:11,701 --> 00:56:13,578
Because you're selfish.

711
00:56:14,871 --> 00:56:16,373
[choking up]
Because I love you.

712
00:56:21,795 --> 00:56:23,797
[whimpers]
In a way you...

713
00:56:25,632 --> 00:56:27,759
you can't understand.

714
00:56:30,678 --> 00:56:31,971
Maybe you never will.

715
00:56:35,475 --> 00:56:37,227
But if that day should come...

716
00:56:40,021 --> 00:56:42,065
if you should ever
have one of your own...

717
00:56:48,655 --> 00:56:49,739
well, then...

718
00:56:54,035 --> 00:56:55,870
I hope you do
a little better than me.

719
00:56:56,996 --> 00:56:58,081
[Ellie sniffling]

720
00:57:02,794 --> 00:57:05,088
[sighs deeply]

721
00:57:13,471 --> 00:57:15,890
I don't think I can
forgive you for this.

722
00:57:25,567 --> 00:57:27,277
But I would like to try.

723
00:57:30,822 --> 00:57:33,825
[♪ gentle music playing]

724
00:57:40,081 --> 00:57:42,083
[rain falling]

725
00:57:44,752 --> 00:57:46,838
[thunder rumbling]

726
00:57:56,806 --> 00:57:58,868
[thunder crashing]

727
00:57:58,892 --> 00:58:01,895
[♪ soft music playing]

728
00:58:07,859 --> 00:58:10,278
[♪ music swells]

729
00:58:14,073 --> 00:58:17,076
[♪ gentle music playing]

730
00:59:24,143 --> 00:59:26,062
[♪ music fades out]

